description.rnr-final-balance: Stock level at the end of the period. =Initial balance + Received - Consumed Â± Adjustments

description.rnr-losses: Manually record losses of this item during the period
description.rnr-low-stock: ! = Final balance is less than half of Maximum, !! = less than quarter

description.rnr-minimum-quantity: The minimum quantity of stock to have on hand. =AMC x Store Preference 'Threshold for Understock'
description.rnr-received: The quantity of this item received during this period (via Inbound Shipments)
description.rnr-requested-quantity: The quantity to be ordered. =Maximum quantity - Final balance
description.suggested-quantity: The number of units which the system has calculated should be ordered
description.supply-quantity: The number of units that will be supplied by this store
description.target-stock: The target stock level for this item, which is the Target MOS * AMC. $t(description.doses-quantity)
description.total-cost: Total value of stock on hand (cost per pack times number of packs)
description.unit-quantity: Total quantity in number of units

To get started, please select the server that you want to connect to.
Once selected, we'll reconnect automatically if that server is available, so you won't need to do this again.
The ðŸ  icon beside a server shows you that this is your local computer.

messages.how-to-read-expiring-items:
Column descriptions: 
* Expiring in (days): Number of days left until batch expires using the expiring items period preference. 
Yellow - batches below the expiring item period. 
Green - anything above the expiring item period. 
Red - expired items. 
* Expected usage: AMC of the item multiplied by the number of months left until expiry. 
* Stock at risk: Quantity of stock that will likely expire before it is used. 
SOH - Expected usage. If the stock is expired, then this should show all SOH for that stock line.
messages.how-to-read-inbound-shipments: This report displays all received inbound shipment lines, which may be filtered by supplier or date range. The total cost is grouped by supplier and item and is displayed only on the final line for each group.
messages.how-to-read-item-usage:
Column descriptions: 
* Stock on order: Sum of quantity in Internal Orders minus any linked Inbound Shipments 
* Months cover: Number of months the current stock is expected to last. The value is 'In stock' / 'AMC'. Note that AMC is calculated using the number of months given by the 'AMC lookback period' shown in the report filter which is configured with the 'monthly consumption lookback period' store preference. A default value will be used if no value is provided in store preference.
messages.how-to-read-outbound-shipments: This report displays all outbound shipment lines, which may be filtered by customer or date range. The total cost is grouped by customer and item and is displayed only on the final line for each group.
messages.how-to-read-pending-encounters:
Days overdue: number of days since scheduled appointment date
Statuses: 
 - Planned: scheduled for a future date, or today 
  - Late: less than 7 days overdue 
  - Lost to Follow Up: more than 7 days overdue
messages.how-to-read-stock-detail: This report has the same information as the stock page without any interactivity.
messages.how-to-read-stock-status:
Status descriptions: 
* Understocked - MOS is lower than min MOS (store preference: threshold for understock) 
* Overstocked - MOS is higher than max MOS (store preference: threshold for overstock) 
* Out of stock - SOH is 0 and AMC is > 0 
* Well stocked - MOS is between min and max MOS 
* No consumption - AMC is 0
